# Context ignore for repo-root-context image builds (rust/Containerfile.controller).
# The Go controller/operator images use controller/ as their context and are
# unaffected. Whitelist style: the Rust image needs only protocol/ and rust/
# (rust/jumpstarter-protocol/build.rs compiles ../../protocol/proto), so
# everything else — notably .git, python/.venv, .e2e — stays out of the
# context tarball. Cargo build-artifact dirs (target, target-codegen, and any
# other target* the FFI/codegen builds create) are large and rebuilt inside the
# image, so they must be excluded or they fill the build VM's disk.
*
!protocol
!rust
rust/target
rust/target-codegen
rust/target-*
**/target/
